# Compose screen structure

Canonical pattern for busy screens: **Screen Context** — full rules in `docs/agents/screen-context.md`.

## Busy screen (default when many components)

```
feature/<name>/presentation/<screen>/
  *ScreenContext.kt  # service, updateState, exits, scope
  *ViewModel.kt      # MutableStateFlow UI state only
  *Screen.kt         # Ctx.Screen(state) + thin @Preview stub
  *Previews.kt       # preview host, fakes, cases
  ui/                # Ctx UI extensions (take state)
  logic/             # Ctx logic extensions
```

- Screen-specific UI/logic = **context extensions**; pass **`state`** into UI composables.
- Designsystem composables keep normal parameters.
- Host builds context with **`remember(…keys)`** + ViewModel; screen does not take a concrete VM.
- **Never nest function declarations.**

## Thin screen (optional)

```
feature/<name>/presentation/<screen>/
  *ViewModel.kt
  *Screen.kt
  *Content.kt        # optional; avoid mega callback lists
```

If Content grows past ~6–8 callbacks, switch to Screen Context.

## ViewModel

- Holds in-memory UI state across config changes only.
- No feature-service calls, validation, or navigation effects in the VM.
- Route args may be constructor params (Koin `parametersOf`).

## Nesting

- Keep composable nesting ≤ **2–3 levels** per function; extract children when deeper.
- Nested *calls* are fine; nested *function definitions* are not.

## Previews

- Cases/fixtures in `*Previews.kt` (`PreviewParameterProvider` is fine).
- Keep a thin `@Preview` stub on `*Screen.kt` so previews sit next to the screen in the IDE.
